cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a method for RGB-D scene semantic segmentation using recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and information transfer layers. The focus is on computer vision and machine learning techniques, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the use of RNNs and information transfer layers suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The application of the proposed method to indoor scene labeling suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
